 {"id":"franken_numpy-ltc4","title":"numpy.array_equiv python wrapper parity","description":"Add fnp_python.array_equiv passthrough wrapper around numpy.array_equiv(a1, a2). True iff arrays are shape-broadcastable AND all element pairs equal. Include oracle test covering: identical shapes equal → True, broadcastable shapes (e.g., (3,) and (1,3)) equal → True, broadcastable but unequal values → False, incompatible shapes → False, scalar vs array → True if all elements equal scalar, NaN behavior (False because NaN != NaN), and integer/float dtype mix.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T10:16:54.768570906Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T11:10:53.820086783Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T11:10:53.818137352Z","close_reason":"Closed by cc-numpy — wrapper fn array_equiv and #[test] parity case array_equiv_matches_numpy_across_broadcast_scalar_object_and_mismatch are present in committed crates/fnp-python/src/lib.rs at HEAD. Acceptance criteria (wrapper exists, oracle test committed) satisfied.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_numpy-lxmb","title":"[PORT-EPIC] numpy.random 100% parity to fnp_python.random","description":"Reach 100% API parity between fnp_python.random and numpy.random.\n\nCurrent state (2026-04-24):\n- BitGenerators ported: MT19937, PCG64 (separate from PCG64DXSM post DISC-008 resolution), PCG64DXSM, Philox, SFC64\n- Classes exposed: SeedSequence, Generator, RandomState, all 5 bit generators\n- Module-level functions: only default_rng()\n- Generator method surface: extensive (~60 distributions), covers all standard numpy.random.Generator methods\n- RandomState method surface: legacy interface ported with rand, randn, randint, random_sample, normal, etc.\n\nRemaining gaps to close for 100% parity:\n1. numpy.random module-level legacy API — numpy.random.rand(...), randn(...), randint(...), random(...), random_sample(...), normal(...), seed(...), get_state(), set_state(...), choice(...), shuffle(...), permutation(...), plus every distribution as a top-level alias. In numpy these delegate to a shared global RandomState singleton. Currently fnp_python.random exposes ZERO of these.\n2. numpy.random.BitGenerator (abstract base class) — numpy exposes it so users can isinstance-check; fnp_python doesn't.\n3. Conformance matrix — no automated audit proving fnp_python.random covers 100% of numpy.random.__all__.\n\nEach sub-bead ships conformance parity tests alongside the port.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-04-24T21:55:09.422242992Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-24T22:19:20.186001861Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T22:19:20.183389154Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
